## Parent App

//text: Fully native iOS and Android apps built for parents to control family spending, set limits, and handle daily banking scenarios.
//note: I was based at the client’s office while managing a remote team of three product designers, as well as illustrators and motion designers.

//text: The core idea was to separate family money from personal accounts, so users could instantly understand what they needed to manage. We supported this separation visually with color zones: blue for family finances and neutral colors for personal finances.


//text: Family owners had full control over spending, while other parent-level users could manage their own finances. Child accounts were created and controlled by the family owner.
//text: At the same time, the bank still needed to support single users, so we designed the full banking app experience — from ordering a card to all key payment scenarios, as well as deposits, loans, and loyalty programs.

