## Child App

//text: Fully native iOS and Android apps built around a savings-first experience. The app offered a focused set of features: topping up a piggy bank, completing tasks, and checking transaction history.
//note: We carefully considered which features would best support children’s financial literacy — without causing harm, and while gradually helping kids understand how money works.

//text: I came up with the idea of a goal-oriented digital piggy bank. For example, a child could save for a dream toy while parents assigned small tasks and goals to help them reach it.

//text: We found that parents were interested in this feature because it helped them learn more about their child’s preferences. They also tended to make tasks easy enough for children to access their money quickly.

//text: On the other hand, older teens could learn how deposits work and invest their pocket money toward larger purchases. Parents had no access to a child’s piggy bank without the child’s permission.
 

